modules.description: Handles incoming HTTP/2 connections on a stream socket. Accepts a request handler to process client requests, an error handler for connection errors, and operates on stream sockets using Eio's networking abstractions. Useful for building HTTP/2 servers that process requests over TCP or Unix domain sockets.

This module implements HTTP/2 client functionality over Eio, managing connections and requests. It provides operations to create connections, send requests with response handlers, and manage connection lifecycle with ping, shutdown, and close-checking operations. Concrete use cases include sending HTTP/2 requests over TLS streams and handling server push and trailers in an asynchronous network client.

Implements HTTP/2 client and server functionality over Eio's network abstractions. The server module handles incoming connections on stream sockets, routing requests through user-provided handlers, while the client module manages outgoing connections, request submission, and connection lifecycle operations. Used for building asynchronous HTTP/2 services and clients with support for TLS, server push, and HTTP/2 trailers.
